  "prompt": "What is full form of hotel?",
  "response": "\"Hotel\" is **not** an acronym; it doesn't have a full form. The word \"hotel\" originates from the French term **\"h\u00f4tel,\"** which historically referred to a large townhouse or a place of residence. Over time, its meaning evolved in English to denote an establishment that provides lodging, accommodations, and various services for travelers and guests.\n\nIf you come across \"HOTEL\" written in all capital letters as an acronym, it might be a backronym\u2014a phrase constructed to fit the existing word\u2014but such usages are not standard and can vary depending on the context. Generally, \"hotel\" is simply a regular word without an expanded form.",
